Class ValidatorsUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • helios.ValidatorsUtil

      • safe

        public static final <T> java.util.List<ValidatorError> safe(T value,
                                                            java.util.function.Predicate<T> cond,
                                                            ValidatorError error)

        Executes safely a given Predicate with a possible null value. If the condition returns true, that means the condition matches the error case, therefore it will return a List with the ValidatorError passed as last parameter.

        Parameters:
        value - The possible null value
        cond - error case condition. If should return true if it matched the error case, false otherwise.
        error - the error to return in case the predicate matches the error condition
        Returns:
        a list of ValidatorError elements.
        Since:
        0.1.0

      • safeCurry

        public static final <A,B> java.util.function.Predicate<B> safeCurry(A param,
                                                                    java.util.function.BiPredicate<A,B> source)

        Given a BiPredicate function, this method applies safely the first param of the predicate and returns the partial applied function. If the first param is null then this method will return a Predicate that always returns false, if the param is not null it will return a Predicate that represents the previous BiPredicate with the first parameter set.

        Parameters:
        param - the first parameter of the BiPredicate
        source - an instance of BiPredicate
        Returns:
        an instance of Predicate.
        Since:
        0.1.0
